President Barack Obama has proclaimed May 2012 as National Building Safety Month. In this proclamation, he emphasizes the importance of implementing building safety solutions to strengthen resilience and meet community needs. By establishing building safety, energy efficiency, and fire prevention codes and standards, professionals in government and industry help save lives and prevent disruption in the aftermath of disasters. The President's administration is committed to advancing this mission by developing public-private partnerships, utilizing science and technology to establish stronger codes and standards, and promoting research and development for innovation in construction and retrofitting techniques. The proclamation encourages all Americans to visit Ready.gov to learn more about preparedness and get involved. Building safety professionals are recognized for their critical role in protecting communities from various disasters, and this proclamation serves as a rededication to ensuring the readiness and resilience of the nation.